gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Kings 125, Jazz 104
gameRecap.excerpt: Led by Keegan Murrays career-high 47 points (16-23 FG, 12-15 3pt. FG), the Kings defeated the Jazz, 125-104. Domantas Sabonis added 20 points, 10 rebounds and eight assists for the Kings, while Collin Sexton tallied a team-high 28 points for the Jazz in the losing effort. The Kings have won back-to-back games and improve to 15-9 on the season, while the Jazz fall to 9-17.
